, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":6,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705197,"age":79,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Conyers was born about 1376, in Durham, England, his father, John Conyers, was 11374 and his mother, Lady Elizabeth Aton, was 26. He had at least 1 daughter with Alliana Cotam."},"et":{"about 1376–":"umbes 1376–Surnud","1376–Male":"1376–Surnud","1381–1431":"1381–1431","1350–1408":"1350–1408","1376–1438":"1376–1438","1323–1395":"1323–1395","1352–1419":"1352–1419","1352":"1352","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1455":"1455","1323":"1323","1376":"1376","about 1369":"umbes 1369","1431":"1431","about 1376":"umbes 1376","1419":"1419","1408":"1408","1438":"1438","Durham, England":"Durham, England"},"fi":{"about 1376–":"noin 1376–Kuollut","1376–Male":"1376–Kuoll